ðŸŽ­ Real-Life Story
Over time, some books in the library become damaged, lost, or outdated.
The librarian wants the ability to remove these books from the system so that the library record stays accurate.

ðŸŽ¯ New Requirement
Add a feature that allows the librarian to delete a book by title.

ðŸ§© Expected Behavior
Librarian selects: Delete Book

System asks:
"Enter the title of the book to remove:"

If book found â†’ remove it from:

The ArrayList

The library.txt file

Display: "Book removed successfully."

If book not found â†’ display: "Book not found."

ðŸ’¡ Learning Outcome
Students practice:

Searching inside ArrayList

Removing objects

Saving updated data to file
